The article is a joint statement by Dmitry A. Medvedev, President of the Russian Federation, and Barack Obama, President of the United States of America, regarding missile defense issues. The statement highlights the intention of both countries to continue discussing cooperation in responding to the challenge of ballistic missile proliferation. They plan to analyze the challenges of the 21st century and prepare recommendations, prioritizing political and diplomatic methods. They also plan to review means of cooperation in monitoring missile programs globally and establish a Joint Data Exchange Center. Both countries express their willingness to cooperate with other countries concerned about missile proliferation and call for refraining from actions that could undermine global stability.